.SH NAME
bb-deployment-environment-variable-delete - Delete a deployment environment variable


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb deployment environment variable delete  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Delete a Bitbucket deployment environment variable by key or UUID. Humans must confirm the exact repository, environment, and variable unless --yes is provided. Scripts and agents should use --yes together with --no-prompt.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--environment\fP=""
	Deployment environment reference as a name, slug, or UUID

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for delete

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target

.PP
\fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Skip the confirmation prompt


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb deployment environment variable delete APP_ENV --repo workspace-slug/pipelines-repo-slug --environment test --yes
  bb --no-prompt deployment environment variable delete '{variable-uuid}' --repo workspace-slug/pipelines-repo-slug --environment test --yes --json '*'
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbb-deployment-environment-variable(1)\fP


